      <hedline>
        <hl1>Online Problems Overseas</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Irene Starr letter comments on July 20 article on using a computer overseas</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Using an unfamiliar foreign-language keyboard layout can make touch typing difficult for those used to an English keyboard. A better option for European languages is to use the Windows United States-International English Keyboard, which uses the punctuation keys as modifiers. Its intuitive method works with most Windows applications, while keeping the familiar ''qwerty'' keyboard.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
